Director Prompt Controls
- Director must not implement code directly.
- Director supervises through slice packets, checkpoint summaries, handoffs, validation evidence, QA reports, and final review.
- Stop if an Orchestrator changes files outside slice scope without explanation.
- Stop if a slice leaves required cleanup for later when the plan makes it an exit gate.
- Stop if validation is missing or only partially run without Director acceptance.
- Stop if MachineDesign truth round-trips through BotBlueprint.
- Stop if deriveControls, cellForMount, foundation rails, or minimum viable loadout logic remain authoritative for machine sessions.
- Stop if replay/browser proof is skipped for replay changes.
- Stop if the final expert review panel is skipped.

Prepared Slice 1 Orchestrator Packet

Slice: 1 - Parameterized Action Submission End-to-End

Goal:
Add parameterized GameMaster action submissions end to end while preserving fixed-action compatibility.

Context:
- ActiveActionSet.actions remains private server authority.
- Public packets may expose only redacted action templates and schemas.
- Submissions may include parameters only when the matched action template defines a schema.
- Request identity and idempotency must hash normalized parameters, not raw JSON.
- Do not pass raw submission.parameters into loadout logic.
- This slice does not implement machine placement behavior beyond a server-owned resolver surface for submitted actions.

Owned files:
- packages/schemas/src/types.ts
- packages/schemas/src/validators/gameMasterAction.ts
- packages/schemas/src/relay.ts
- packages/schemas/src/agentSamples.ts
- apps/worker/src/session.ts
- apps/web/src/agent/agentClient.ts
- apps/web/src/agent/agentClientTypes.ts
- apps/web/src/agent/agentRoleApiInstaller.ts
- focused tests in tests/ if needed for the required coverage

Must add:
- GameMasterActionSubmission.parameters?: Record<string, unknown>
- GameMaster legal action parameterSchema and parameterExamples support
- resolveSubmittedGameAction or equivalent server-owned resolver
- normalized parameter hashing used by action locks/idempotency
- template/schema validation for parameters

Must delete or update:
- Agent-facing "actionId only" guidance.
- Client allowlists that reject parameters.
- Any server path that treats parameterized submissions as raw JSON payload passthrough.

Forbidden shortcuts:
- Do not validate parameters only in the client.
- Do not accept parameters when the selected action has no parameter schema.
- Do not ignore unknown parameters.
- Do not hash raw JSON or rely on insertion order.
- Do not let same actionId with different normalized parameters reuse the same lock.

Acceptance criteria:
- Fixed legacy/fixed actions still work without parameters.
- Unknown parameter rejects.
- Missing required parameter rejects.
- Out-of-range parameter rejects.
- Normalized equivalent parameters hash the same.
- Different normalized parameters for the same action conflict with an existing lock.
- Web client accepts parameters.
- Web client still rejects unsupported fields.
- No unmodified agent-facing "actionId only" guidance remains.

Required validation:
- rg -n "actionId only|Submit the actionId only|accepts only action, actionSetId, decisionVersion, actionId" packages apps tests
- npm.cmd test

Required handoff:
- Changed files.
- Tests run and validation output summary.
- Remaining legacy matches from the required rg command.
- Any risks/blockers.
- Exact deviations from the slice packet, if any.

Prepared Slice 2 Orchestrator Packet

Slice: 2 - System-Owned Machine Core and MachineDesign Storage

Goal:
Introduce a system-owned immutable Machine Core and make MachineDesign the stored authority for new sessions.

Context:
- MachineDesign is authoritative for new machine sessions.
- BotBlueprint and BotDesignSnapshot are legacy projections only after this migration; do not round-trip MachineDesign through them to recover truth.
- The core is system-owned, immutable, free, not inventory, not a shop/catalog body part, and starts as instance id "core".
- Bad machines may be legal if physically valid; do not add strategic viability checks in this slice.
- Slice 1 parameterized submission support is already present; do not rewrite it unless required for compile compatibility.

Owned files:
- packages/schemas/src/types.ts
- packages/sim/src/machineDesign.ts
- packages/sim/src/index.ts
